{"title_page": "The Collection (1991 Boney M. album)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Collection\n| type       = Compilation\n| artist     = [[Boney M.]]\n| cover      = Boney M. - The Collection (1991).jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1991\n| recorded   = 1976-80\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Reggae]], [[Euro disco]], [[R&B]]\n| length     = 40:45\n| label      = [[BMG-Ariola]] <small>(FRG)</small>\n| producer   = [[Frank Farian]]\n| prev_title = Greatest Hits of All Times \u2013 Remix '89 \u2013 Volume II\n| prev_year  = 1989\n| next_title = [[Daddy Cool \u2013 Star Collection]]\n| next_year  = 1991\n}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Cristal Collection (1994)\n| type       = Compilation\n| artist     = [[Boney M.]]\n| cover      = Boney M. - Cristal Collection.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   =\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Sunny, Daddy Cool, Rivers Of Babylon (2001)\n| type       = Compilation\n| artist     = [[Boney M.]]\n| cover      = Boney M. - Sunny, Daddy Cool, Rivers Of Babylon (2001).jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   =\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = L'Essentiel (2001)\n| type       = Compilation\n| artist     = [[Boney M.]]\n| cover      = Boney M. - L'Essentiel.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   =\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1=[[Allmusic]]\n|rev1Score={{Rating|3|5}} <ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r350041}}</ref> <ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r573127}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''The Collection''' is a [[compilation album]] of recordings by [[Boney M.]] released by label [[BMG-Ariola]] in 1991. <br />\n''The Collection'' was part of [[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]]'s first mid-price CD campaign, the company released many ''Collection''s containing back-catalogue material by artists ranging from [[Modern Talking]], Imagination and [[Amanda Lear]] to [[Chuck Berry]], [[Glenn Miller]] and [[Elvis Presley]]. <br />\nThe majority of the tracks on this release are taken from 1980 compilation ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]'', subsequently most of them appear in slightly edited form.<br />\nBMG-Ariola France has re-issued this compilation with new artwork as ''Cristal Collection'' in 1994 and as ''Sunny, Daddy Cool, Rivers Of Babylon'' and ''L'Essentiel'', both in 2001.\n\n== Track listing ==\n#\"[[Rivers of Babylon]]\" (Farian, Reyam) - 3:59\n#* Edited version from ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''\n#\"Daddy Cool\"  (Farian, Reyam) - 3:25\n#* Original album version\n#\"[[Sunny (Bobby Hebb song)|Sunny]]\"  ([[Bobby Hebb]]) - 3:14\n#* Edited version ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''\n#\"[[My Friend Jack]]\" ([[The Smoke]]) - 4:31\n#* Edited album version from ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''\n#\"I See a Boat on the River\" (Farian, Jay, Rulofs) - 3:03\n#* Edited version from ''[[Fantastic Boney M.]]''\n#\"[[Brown Girl in the Ring (song)|Brown Girl in the Ring]]\" (Farian) - 3:06\n#* Edited version from ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''\n#\"[[Mary's Boy Child]]/Oh My Lord\"  ([[Jester Hairston]], Farian, Jay, Lorin) -  4:31\n#* Edited version from ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''\n#\"Bahama Mama\" (Farian, Jay) - 3:17\n#* ''[[Oceans Of Fantasy]]'' album edit\n#\"I'm Born Again\" (Jay, Rulofs) - 3:57\n#* Edited version from ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''\n#\"Oceans of Fantasy\" (Kawohl & Towers) - 3:19\n#* Edited version from ''[[The Magic of Boney M. - 20 Golden Hits]]''\